                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_108144">Broughton</placeName>.

   <persName>
                           <forename>Gregory</forename> 
                           <surname>Grimbaut</surname>
                        </persName> grants to <orgName key="org_108004">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                        </orgName> in free alms 42d. rent from the land which <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> de <surname>fonte</surname>
                        </persName> once held from him in <placeName key="place_108144">Brouton</placeName>, as appears in another charter concerning the same gift. Every year the monks are to distribute 13d. of this to the poor (<hi rend="italic">die absolucionis</hi>), and 2/5 is to provide a lamp before the altar of S. Mary, burning throughout the night, and at all masses during the day. 
   Witnesses: <persName>Sir <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>fitz-Simon</surname>, lord of D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                        </persName>, 
